The National Chairman of the Social Exchange Market Certified Chairmen Association (SEMCCA), Engr. Theophilus Chukwuemeka has disclosed that a world charity organization has concluded plans to disburse soft grant to about 30 million Nigerians. Chukwuemeka said the grant meant for those operating a small scale business will take a bottom up approach to the beneficiaries. Speaking in Abeokuta, Ogun State capital at the convergence of over 2,500 leaders of SEMCCA across the country, the Chairman explained that the grant would assist the Federal government to alleviate poverty in Nigeria. The SEMCCA Chairman equally noted that, the grant would empower the beneficiaries and reduce the crime rate in the country as majority of the youths who had applied for the grant through SEMCCA will have enough capital to invest in their businesses. Speaking on the alleged embezzlement scandal against the grant facilitator, Donald Olorunkeyede, Chukwuemeka said the entire leadership of SEMCCA had passed a vote of confidence on the facilitator. 30m Nigerians to get soft grant, says SEMCCA Chairman 80 entrepreneurs benefit from FGâ€™s employment grants - Enelamah 600 widows, less privileged in 4 LGAs get support Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin